This paper is about image aesthetics assessment using deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of pretrained deep learning models and support vector machines, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper analyzes the contribution of local and scene-aware information, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
